trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> objects.
This class cannot be inherited.

The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleActionCollection> collection allows access to the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction> elements of the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HttpModulesSection> section.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleActionCollection"></xref> class.
This constructor creates a non-initialized instance of the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleActionCollection> object.
Adds an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> object to the collection.
Adds an <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction> object to the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> module to add to the collection.
An attempt was made to add an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> object that already exists in the collection.
Removes all <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> objects from the collection.
This method inserts a `clear` directive into the appropriate section of the configuration file to clear all references to elements defined in a higher-level configuration file.
All elements defined in the appropriate section of the current configuration file are removed.
Gets the collection index of the specified <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> module.
Before using this method, you must identify an <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction> module with the proper name and type.
You can then use this module object to get its collection index.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> module for which to get the collection index.
The collection index value for the specified module.
Gets or sets an item in this collection.
This property is intended for internal use only.
Module collection index.
The item at the specified index.
Removes an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> object from the collection.
This method inserts a `<remove>` element into the appropriate section of the configuration file for any element defined in a higher-level configuration file.
If the element is defined in the appropriate section of the current configuration file, its entry is removed from the configuration file.
The object to remove must exist in the collection.
The key that identifies the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> object to remove from the collection.
There is no <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> object with the specified key in the collection, the element has already been removed, or the collection is read-only.
Removes an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> object from the collection.
This method inserts a `<remove>` element into the appropriate section of the configuration file for any element defined in a higher-level configuration file.
If the element is defined in the appropriate section of the current configuration file, its entry is removed from the configuration file.
The object to remove must exist in the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> module to remove.
The passed <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> object does not exist in the collection, the element has already been removed, or the collection is read-only.
Removes an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> module at the specified index from the collection.
This method inserts a `<remove>` element into the appropriate section of the configuration file for any element defined in a higher-level configuration file.
If the element is defined in the appropriate section of the current configuration file, its entry is removed from the configuration file.
The object to remove must exist in the collection.
The index of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> module to remove.
There is no <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.HttpModuleAction"></xref> object at the specified index in the collection, the element has already been removed, or the collection is read-only.
